27/03/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- British Minister for Europe Geoff Hoon reaffirmed his country's support for Croatia's aspirations to join the EU and NATO, during a daylong visit to Zagreb on Monday (March 26th).
Hoon, who met with the Foreign and European Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic, Prime Minister Ivo Sanader and President Stipe Mesic, stressed that his country views Croatia as a strategic partner.
He added that Croatia has made considerable progress in meeting the criteria for EU accession.
(HINA, HRT - 26/03/07)
